This is a simple form with a few functions for converting opcodes as server sees them to/from various values used by WoW client.
Don't expect it to magically give you all the opcodes.
Currently for version 4.0.6.

Fields exaplanation:
Opcode (hex/decimal) - opcode as sends sends and recieves it.
Offset (dec) - offset of the handler in client packet handler table.
Converted (dec) - intermediate value for calculating the Offset.
Special (hex) - value used in NetClient__ProcessSpecialOpcodes.